info.name: Peda
info.description: Serves 1 | a sweet dish hailing from the indian subcontinent. It originated from mathura, uttar pradesh, india. Usually prepared in thick, semi-soft pieces, its main ingredients are khoa, sugar and traditional flavorings including cardamom seeds, pistachio nuts and saffron.

info.name: Motichoor Laddu
info.description:
Serves 1 | Droplets of gram flour meet pure deshi ghee and sweet syrup to form everybody's favourite celebration sweet! Fulfill your cravings with this laddoo that has elaichi and magaz kheera for traditional goodness.
.

info.name: Besan Laddu
info.description: Serves 1 | Besan laddu is a popular indian sweet dish made of besan (chickpea flour or gram flour), sugar, and ghee. Besan is roasted in ghee till golden brown appearance with a nutty fragrance.

info.name: Sweet Boondi
info.description: Serves 1 | an indian dessert made from sweetened, fried chickpea flour.

info.name: Sev Boondi
info.description: Serves 1 | Sev and Boondi are two different words joined together to make a sweet called Sev Boondi. Sweet Boondi / Meethi Boondi is an Indian sweet recipe with a crisper surface and sugary juice within mixed with sev made from plain flour. It is served as prasad during festivals or as a sweet munch after meals.

info.name: Jalebi
info.description: Serves 1 | A delicious dish made by deep-frying maida flour (plain flour or all-purpose flour) batter in pretzel or circular shapes, which are then soaked in sugar syrup.

info.name: Imarti
info.description: Serves 1 | imarti or jhangri is a dessert popular in india and other countries of the indian subcontinent. It is made by deep-frying urad flour batter in a kind of circular flower shape, then soaked in sugar syrup. Alternative names include amriti, emarti, omriti and jaangiri.

info.name: Kesar Kaju Katli
info.description: Serves 1 | Kesar kaju katli is a tasty variant of ever famous kaju katli or vegan cashew fudge. Kesar kaju katli is a very expensive sweet found in select sweet shops. The addition of saffron simply takes this sweet to a whole new level.

info.name: Kaju Katli (100 Gm)
info.description: Serves 1 | Kaju katli, also known as kaju barfi, is a traditional indian dessert characterized by its diamond shape, made with cashew nuts, sugar, cardamom powder, and ghee butter. This sweet treat often comes wrapped in an edible silver foil, signifying luxury and appreciation for the consumer.

info.name: Kesar Kaju Katli (100 Gm)

info.name: Anjeer Roll /Anjeer King
info.description: Serves 1 | Sweet in taste that give a delicious flavor and are highly appreciated for their purity and mouthwatering taste. Available in cashew, mango, rose, kiwi and strawberry flavours, this sweet array can be served in all kinds of festivals and other various occasions.

info.name: Besan Laddu (pure Ghee)
info.description: Serves 1 | Besan ladoo are round sweet balls made by roasting gram flour and ghee together, and then adding sugar to make a thick pasty dough that is then formed into delicious, melt-in-your-mouth balls.

info.name: Lahsun Chiwda
info.description: Serves 1 | Lasun chivda or garlic chivda is carefully made from pressed rice, curry leaves, spices, and garlic powder.

info.name: Chakli ( Murukku )
info.description: Serves 1 | Chakli is typically made from flours of rice, bengal gram (brown chickpea) and black gram (urad daal). It has several variations, depending on the types and proportion of flours used. Murukku, a similar snack typically made without the Bengal gram flour, is also sometimes called "chakli".

info.name: Bhakarwadi
info.description: Serves 1 | Bakarwadi is made from gram flour dough made into spirals stuffed with a mixture of coconut, poppy seeds and sesame seeds. It is then fried until it gets crispy. It can be stored for weeks and enjoyed as an evening snack.

info.name: Nylon Sev
info.description: Serves 1 | Nylon Sev is a thin strands-like snack typically used for chaats like Sev Batata Puri, Bhel, etc.

info.name: Tikha Gathiya
info.description: Serves 1 | Gathiya is a classic deep-fried savoury snack, which is made of gram flour flavoured with ajwain.

info.name: Mahalaxmi chivda
info.description: Serves 1 | Mahalaxmi Chivda contains rice flakes and mixed with other ingredients. It is crunchy and crispy treat containing a delight combination of flavours that is sweet and salty.

info.name: Makai Chivda
info.description: Serves 1 | Cornflakes chivda or makai chivda is a deep-fried savory mixture with a sweet, spicy and slightly tangy taste.

info.name: Diet chivda
info.description: Serves 1 | Diet Chivda is a crunchy mix of rice flakes and other tasty ingredients. it can be eaten as a standalone snack or with tea. This crunchy savoury delight is flavourful bringing forward the perfect snacking experience.

info.name: Khara Boondi
info.description: Serves 1 | Kara boondi is a spiced version of boondi and a mixture consisting of boondi .

info.name: Shakkar Para

info.name: Namak Para
info.description: Serves 1 | Namak Para is a traditional Indian snack. It is made with midly-salted and spiced flour fried to perfection. It is crisp, crunchy and oozes flavors .
